(Alcan Aluminium Ltd) is closing itsaluminum smelter in Ludwigshafen, West Germany this June due tohigh operating costs, an Alcan spokesman said.    The smelter, near Frankfurt, had annual capacity of about44,000 metric tons but was operating at about half that inJanuary, spokesman Fernand Leclerc said.    Leclerc said Alcan decided it would cost too much tomodernize the plant.    He said there is a possibility the company will sell thesmelter, which currently employs 320 people, before itsscheduled closing.              Reuter&#3;